# Documentation · Architecture Decisions (ADR)

## Where to put documentation

- Organize under the **project root** or `docs/` by purpose (e.g., `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/adr/`).
- Keep the **README** for execution steps, environment variables, and deployment overview. If it grows, link to `docs/`.

## ADR (Architecture Decision Record)

- **When to use it**: when you make a **hard-to-revert decision**, such as stack choices, authentication approach, state management, or folder structure changes.
- **Format**: write a short record containing number, title, status (proposed/accepted/discarded), context, decision, and outcome (e.g., `docs/adr/0001-use-next-app-router.md`).

## Relationship to code comments

- Use comments only when they add value (even a single line) about *why* something was done. If a comment would duplicate an ADR, point to the ADR and keep the code comment short.

## Summary

Leave major decisions in ADRs, and reduce onboarding + maintenance cost via README and `docs/`.
